{"parse":{"title":"Wit's End","pageid":3583,"wikitext":"{{Item info\n|goldvalue = \n{{gold value|Fray Gold Value|nolink=}}\n* 45 [[on-hit]] [[magic damage]] = {{g|{{#expr:{{#var:ohdmg}}*45 round2}}}}\n** '''Total Gold Value''' = {{g|{{#vardefineecho:total|{{#expr:{{#var:total}}+{{#var:ohdmg}}*45 round 2}}}}}}\n|goldefficiency =\n|similaritems = Terminus;Blade of the Ruined King;Guinsoo's Rageblade;Kraken Slayer;Nashor's Tooth;Maw of Malmortius;Mercury's Treads;Sterak's Gage;Endless Hunger;Mercurial Scimitar\n|background = \n|notes =\n* {{sbc|Fray}} deals {{tip|proc damage}}, and thus will not trigger [[spell effects]].\n* {{sbc|Fray's}} on-hit damage does not apply to [[structure]]s.\n* The bonus damage dealt by {{sbc|Fray}} benefits from {{stil|life steal}}.\n|strategy = \n* {{ii|Wit's End}} is both an offensive and defensive item for magic damage; it provides magic damage on-hit while also resisting magic damage taken.\n* {{ii|Wit's End}} can be purchased on physical damage attackers to counter enemies with high amounts of armor with its passive that deals magic damage.\n|trivia = \n* Previously, '''Wit's End''' gave 42 on-hit magic damage and attack speed. Considering the item's name, this was probably a reference to {{w|The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy}}, where 42 is the answer to \"the Ultimate Question of Life, the Universe, and Everything\".\n* {{ii|Nashor's Tooth}} is the ability power counterpart to {{ii|Wit's End}}.\n[[File:Void Crest icon.png|link=Void#Trivia|100px|center]]\n|media = \n<gallery captionalign=\"center\" orientation=\"square\" spacing=\"small\">\nHearthbound Axe item screenshot.png|Old Movement Speed VFX\nWit's End screenshot.png|Old Item VFX\n</gallery>\n|revisions = \n|patchhistory = \n;[[V14.19]]\n* Combine cost increased to {{g|550}} from {{g|500}}.\n** Total cost unchanged.\n* Attack speed reduced to 50% from 55%.\n* Magic resistance reduced to 45 from 50.\n* Fray damage changed to 45 at all levels from {{pp|40 to 80 for 11|1;9 to 1